{
  "message": "fuzz(btrfs-tree-log): 20 structured seeds across topology \u00d7 corruption\n\nExisting 7 seeds left the topology \u00d7 corruption \u00d7 leaf-shape phase\nspace sparsely covered. Add 20 seeds that pin the harness's three\ntopologies (Absent / SingleLeaf / InternalTwoLeaf) against each of\nthe five corruption modes (None / BadChecksum / Structural /\nUncoveredRoot / UnsupportedChecksum) plus key leaf-shape boundaries:\n\n  * Absent \u00d7 {None, BadChecksum, Structural, UncoveredRoot, Unsupported}\n  * SingleLeaf with 0 / 1 / 6 entries\n  * SingleLeaf with each of the four item types (INODE/DIR/EXTDATA/XATTR)\n  * SingleLeaf with payload lengths 0, 4, 16, 32, 40, 47 (near 48 cap)\n  * InternalTwoLeaf with {0,0}, {1,1}, {3,3}, {0,3} child counts\n  * Each topology paired with its applicable corruption modes\n\n266K runs / 16s post-seed surface no crashes.",
